messages.message:
regarding this, i have a pr up to fix some unittests + get them to run in ci https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/73384/files

having fixed mypy issues w/ genai/langchain and including those in `third-party/bazel/py` , unittests w/ bazel are running and mostly passing except for some in flow_handler and flow_export ones that need to be fixed

yet, for anything that is non-bazel, tests are failing w `ImportError: cannot import name 'genai' from 'google' (unknown location)` some of these have their own poetry files so i imagine we just add the packages there, but for things like flow/server and connector-utils w/o poetry files, how do we include these dependencies?
